inn1.comm: on target straight away, pitches just short of a length on middle and leg and angles across Gayle who defends on the back foot back to the bowler, the bounce appears to be rather low
there's that low bounce again, pitches on leg and middle and angles across Gayle, it doesn't get up higher than shin-height, Gayle pushes at it and the ball runs off the edge down to third man
Chanderpaul gets off the mark by flicking that off his pads down to fine leg, Gul's line was awry that time, pitching it outside leg and a touch too short
beaten, and by an awesome ball, that pitched on a perfect length on off stump and drew Gayle forward, it seamed away from the left-hander off the pitch and whizzed past the outside edge
poor line, pitching outside leg stump and Gayle whips that off his pads behind square for a single
on a good length on off stump, Chanderpaul defends to point
that's straight, just short of a length and kept very low, Gayle manages to keep it out
again the ball keeps low, not very promising at all I'm afriad, Gayle plays it to midwicket for a single
defended to mid-off on the front foot, playing forward will be the order of the day
wider outside the off stump, left alone by the batsman
again Rana Naved pitches it wide outside the off and Chanderpaul shoulders arms
the length is a fraction too full and the line is far too straight, whipped down to fine leg for a single
pushed through extra cover for two runs
a fraction too short and Chanderpaul is very quick to rock back and pull it for four, he got into position superbly to play that shot
and again, this time it isn't that short really but Chanderpaul still maganes to whips it through square leg, that's how good this pitch is, ideal for batting apart from the occasional low bounce
defended to cover on the front foot
pushed on the off side on the back foot
Gayle gets into the act, picthes on off stump at a very drivable length and Gayle leans forward and times it sweetly wide of the fielder at mid-off, Inzamam gives chase but can't catch up
slower ball outside the off stump, left alone
excellent line and length, pitching on middle going straight through, Gayle defends on the front foot

gone, hit plumb in ront, Rana Naved bowling from over the wicket pitched that on middle stump, it straightened just a fraction and Gayle got half-forward and played down the wrong line, Umpire Asad Rauf had a very easy decision to make
beaten first up, Rana Naved got that to swing away from the right-hander after pitching outside off stump, Simmons pushed forward and the ball beat the edge
excellent length and a tight line angling into Simmons' off stump, the batsman did well to get forward and defend solidly with the bat close to the pad
a touch short and angling across the left-hander from over the wicket, Chanderpaul moves towards the ball and guides it down to third man

ooh, the inside edge lets him off the hook, Simmons moved across his stumps against a  ball that pitched outside off and cut back in to him, he got an inside edge through midwicket for a single, had he missed it would ahve been a close lbw call
better looking stroke, pushed firmly to covers on the front foot
moves acroos his stumps and pushes it to mid-on
left alone outside the off stump
slower ball, pitching just short of a length, it gripped the surface and bounced a little higher than Simmons expected, defended on the leg side
picthes too short and strays on to the pads, easy meat for Chanderpaul who flicks through square leg for two
a touch too short and the angle across the left-hander gives Chanderpaul the room to free his arms and slice it behind point
quicker ball from Rana Naved, pitches outside off and shapes away from the right-hander, Simmons pushes hard at it and gets beaten
much straighter line, on middle stump, defended back to the bowler
pushed to mid-on for a single
cut to deep point, that was the slower ball but Chanderpaul picked it up early
pushed to covers on the front foot
tight line on off stump, giving Simmons no room to work with, he's looking a little ginger as he pushed that to mid-on

shot, that ball was too full and Simmons creamed it at Inzamam at cover who did well to stop it for it was hit with power, Inzamam grimaces after stopping that, remember that he's just recovered froma  finger injury
played wide of the fielder at mid-on for a single
far too short outside off and the poor length allows Simmons to wait on the back foot and punch it through covers for two
that's better, a good length on off stump, pushed back to the bowler on the front foot
Rana Naved strays on the fuller side outside off stump, Chanderpaul leans forward and punches it towards cover but doesn't pierce the infield
good length ball, angling away from the left-hander, left alone
fullish ball outside off stump, Chanderpaul tries to force it through cover on the front foot but gets an inside edge on to his pad
banged in short and Chanderpaul leans out of the way, the ball passes by his ears
short of a length ball on off stump, Chanderpaul opens the blade and guides it in front of point, Shoaib Malik does superbly to dive to his left and cut off runs
defended to mid-off on the front foot

and he receives a thumoing welcome, pitched far toos hirt and outside off stump, Simmons waits for it and drives off the back foot through cover point, Shoaib Malik is in hot pursuit but the ball beats him
better lne and length this time, Simmons defends back to the bowler on the front foot
wide outside the of stump, too wide
a fraction too short again and on off stump, punched to mid-off on the back foot

my this is a fast outfield, Sami again offers a short and wide ball for Simmons to hit, which he promptly does by lashing it just wide of the fielder at third man, the ball flew across the turf and the fielder had no chance
defended back to the bowler
defended on the back foot to the off side, nine runs of Sami's first over
good length outside the off stump, Chanderpaul drives on the front foot to the fielder at short cover

remarkable change of pace, less than 100kmh, Rana Naved delivered that from the back of the hand and the ball dipped in the air as it headed  for middle stump, Chanderpaul spotted that early and played it to midwicket for a single
fired down leg side at 134 kmh, wide called
driven on the back foot to mid-off
fuller length outside the off stumpa dn Simmons gives it a thump to Hafeez at short extra cover
excellent change of pace again and superb fielding from Hafeez at short extra cover, Simmons gave that a meaty blow but Hafeez reached out and stopped it with his left hand
ends the over with a yorker aimed at the base of middle and leg stump, dug out to Hafeez at ...short extra cover
blocked on the back foot
defended to midwicket
a fraction short from Sami on Chanderpaul's hips and he flicks that through midwicket, Inzamam races after it, really races after it, and keeps it down to two runs
better line and length from Sami concentrating on the off stump, Chanderpaul defends on the off side
tight line again and a good length as well, Chanderpaul can't free his arms so he pushes it on the leg side
strays slightly on to the pads, Chanderpaul whips it to square leg but finds the fielder
strays down leg side, wide called
strays on the fuller side just outside of stump, Simmons hits on the up through cover
Smashing shot, similar to the previous one but with a lot more power, the fielders didn't even move as the ball sped away to the cover fence
left alone outside off stump, that wasn't wide enough to cut or full enough to drive
pushed through midwicket for a single
good length and the line is middle and off stump, pushed to mid-on on the back foot
pitches on leg and middle and Chanderpaul forces it off the back foot to midwicket
loose ball, short and wide outside the of stump, Simmons should have cashed in but he tried to hit it too hard and mis-timed it to point
far better line and length, angling into the right-hander, pushed to mid-on
fullish length slanting into the right-hander's middle and leg stump, Simmons punches to mid-on
width offered outside the off stump, Simmons drives to covers, he looks very confortable outside the off stump but is rather edgy when the ball is angled on middle and leg stump
short of a length ball on off and middle stump, defended on the back foot

played on! the length wasn't very good from Sami, on the shorter side outside the off stump, but it was the offcutter and Simmons played away from his body, tried to hit it too hard through cover, he got an inside edge and it cannoned into off stump
hits a good length first ball, angling across the left-hander, defended on the back foot
pitches too shrt and the slant across the left-hander gives Chanderpaul enough room to run it down to third man
quicker ball pitching on a good length and hurrying Samuels into the back foot defence
edged through the vacant slip cordon, that pitched on off stump, drew Samuels forward and moved away off the pitch and took the edge, Razzaq dives on the boundary and just pulls it inside the fence
defended on the front foot
fired down leg side, that swung from leg stump and strayed fown leg side
more swing from Gul, from off outside off stump into Samuel's blockhole, it ended up as a full toss and Samuels did well to dig it out to mid on
wide outside off stump, wide called
short of a length angling into the pads, tucked off the hips through square leg for one
pitches just outside off stump and moves off the pitch, drawing Chanderpaul forward and beating the edge

superb ball, pitching on the perfect length and shaping away from the left-hander, Chanderpaul got squared up and the ball rips past the outside edge, the Pakistanis shout a loud appeal but the umpire says not out
defnded on the leg side
Sami errs on the shorter side and Chanderpaul flicks off his hips to square leg
defended to midwicket, Sami finishes an excellent over, those two balls with which he beat chanderpaul were outstanding
short of a length outside off stump, Samuels opens the face and guides it past point
Gul oversteps, driven to cover on the front foot

short ball angling across Chanderpaul who is very quick to get into position by moving towards the ball, he cuts it through the infield at point, Inzamam gives chase but Sami runs across from third man and picks it up inside the fence
defended to square leg on the back foot
defended on the off side on the back foot
full length outside off stump, driven to cover on the front foot
good ball to finish the over, pitches on a good length and angles into Samuels' off stump, defended on the front foot to cover
driven to point on the front foot, Sami is angling it across Chanderpaul from over the wicket
width offered outside the off stump, Chanderpaul drives at it but gets a thick edge down to third man
punched off the back foot to cover
pitches short of a length outside off stump, Samuels punches on the up and it's a touch uppish as it goes to short cover
full length outside the off stump, very driveable and Samuels obliges by going down on one knee and playing the cover drive but doesn't beat the in field
super shot, that wasn't a bad ball at all, Samuels punched that past Sami and timed it well enough to beat Razzaq at mid-on, who really should have made a better attempt, for four
inside edge on to pad, it would have been close if not for the edge
pitches wide outside the off stump, left alone by the batsman
fullish length on the pads, Chanderpaul whips it off his toes but doesn't beat midwicket
slower ball on leg stump, Chanderpaul moves across and plays it very fine down to fine leg, the stroke wasn't timed perfectly adn that allows Razzaq to pick it up
short of a length on middle and leg, dabbed to midwicket
good length, pitching on leg and middle and finishing up just outside Chanderpaul's off, defended on the back foot
pitches on a good lenth and cuts back into the right-hander from off stump, Samuels waits on the back foot and defends
half-volley angling into off and middle stump, Samuels smashes it back past the bowler, he hit that so hard that mid-off had no chance
defended on the back foot, that was a better length from Sami and the line was on middle stump
pushed to gully
slower ball and Samuels was early on the shot, the ball looped slowly in the air but fell short of the fielder at mid-on
fullish length on leg and middle, flicked off the pads but straight to midwicket
Razzaq oversteps, Chanderpaul opens the face and pushes it to point
tight line and length outside Chanderpaul's off stump, giving him no room at all, defended to cover
fullish length outside off stump, Chanderpaul moves on to the front foot and defends to the off side
driven on the back foot to mid-off
pushed to mid-off on the back foot, Razzaq is just concentraing on keeping it outside the off stump to Chanderpaul
defended back to the bowler
short ball and wide outside the off stump, Samuels goes back and drives on the back foot, the timing was spot on but the placement wasn't, Mohammad Yousuf fields at cover point
defended back to the bowler, Sami is keeping it tight aroud the off stump
dropped slightly short on off stump, punched down to lon-off on the back foot for a single, the run-rate is now below four an over
straying on to the pads, whipped down to fine leg for another single
too straight again from Sami, Samuels works that off his pads to midwicket
fullish length outside off stump, driven to mid-off for a quick single
full and on off stump, Chanderpaul slashes at it and opens the face at the last minute by taking one hand off the bat, the edge flies down to the third man fence
pushed to covers on the front foot, Inzamam has lept the off side field packed for Chanderpaul
driven to Inzamam at cover on the front foot
good length ball, angling across Chanderpaul who drives again on the up but doesn't beat the infield
SHOT, Razzaq offered the batsman the room to free his arms and Chanderpaul drives through cover and finds the gap in a crowded circle, four runs
short of a lengtj, Chanderpaul moves across and flicks behind square, Razzaq oversteps on the last ball, sloppy stuff
pushed wide of the fielder at mid-of for a single
floated through the air outside off stump and spins into Chanderpaul who gets forward and defends
wide outside off stump, left alone
too wide outside off stump yet again, Chanderpaul runs it down to third man
defended back to the bowler
drifting into Samuels from round the wicket, pitching on middle and leg and spinning towards off, pushed back to the bowler on the back foot
straying on to the pads this time, worked to square leg for a single
wide outside the off stump and Samuels thrashes at it, gets a thick bottom edge to the left of Kamran Akmal and down to the fine leg fence
defended to point on the back foot
full length and it swings back into Samuels who defends to mid-on
shortish length outside off stump, Samuels opens the face to run it down to third man
defended back to Razzaq on the back foot
edged but short of Akmal behind the stumps, that was pitched on off and moved away from Chanderpaul who drove loosely at it, lucky for him, unlucky for Pakistan
defended to cover on the back foot
defended behind square on the off side
drifting on to middle and leg, pushed to the vacant midwicket region for a single
that one spun quite a long way from outside Chanderpaul's off stump, he moved across his stumps and got hit on the pad for a leg bye to short fine leg
fired in quick outside off stump, left alone
Samuels steps down the track but doesn't get to the pitch of the ball, he improvises well to open the face and play it to short third man
pitches outside leg stump on a good length, chanderpaul moves across to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad, Razzaq thinks he has a case for lbw but the umpire doesn't
pushed to mid-on on the front foot
slower ball from Razzaq and Chanderpaul waits for it and pushes it back to him
a touch shorter outside the off stump, Chanderpaul plays back and drives to cover
full length outside the off stump, Chanderpaul gets on the front foto and drives to mid-off, the pressure is growing now for no runs ahve been scored off this over so far
Razzaq completes a maiden, Chanderpaul drives the last ball to covers

stumped! Classic dismissal, Rehman drifted that ball in to Samuels from round the wicket, Samuels took a half step down and wasn't to the pitch of the ball, it pitched on leg and middle and spun across the face of the bat, Akmal completes the stumping
quicker through the air on off stump, defended on the front foot
fuller ball outside off stump, Lara pushes it back past the bowler to get off the mark
too short outside off stump, Chanderpaul moves across the stumps and flicks to midwicket
defended to square leg
fuller length on off stump, driven on the off side
lovely shot for a single, Razzaq pitched that on a good length on off stump, Lara got forward and eased it though covers
poor ball, width offered outside the off stump and it's far too short, Chanderpaul opens the face and times it wonderfully to the point fence, superb timing and with that stroke he moves on to 49
flicked off the pads through square leg and that is his second consecutive fifty, well played
defended back to the bowler
short of a length on off stump, cut to point on the back foot&
slower ball on middle and off, Lara waits for it, moves across and works it to fine leg for a single
floated trhough the air outside off stump, that spins back into Lara who backs away and cuts through point for a single
dabbed to short third man for a quick single
defended back to the bowler on the front foot
fullish ball outside off stumop, driven through point for another single
defended on the front foot, Chanderpaul didn't get to the pitch of that one as it pitched outside the off stump and spun back to hit the pad
worked through midwicket for a single
short of a length on middle and leg stump, Chanderpaul moves across but doesn't connect well with the flick, collects a single behind square
defended to point on the front foot
nippy pae at 133 kmh, that pitched on a good length on off stump and moved away from Lara who tried to flick but got beaten
width offered outside off stump and Lara cuts down to third man for two runs, the batsmen ran hard to complete the double
pushed to square leg for a single
excellent timing, Razzaq strays on to the pads and Chanderpaul flicks that through midwicket for four
another no-ball off the last ball of the over, defended to mid-on
full ball outside off, driven hard to the fielder at mid-off who fumbles to allow the single
pushed flat through the air on off stump, Chanderpaul moves across, goes down on one knee and paddles it down to fine leg
short ball outside off stump, Lara lashes it through point with his high back lift and exaggerated bat swing, very pleasing to watch
defended on the front foot
flicked to square leg off his pads
tossed up on off and middle stump, defended on the front foot
pushed wide of the fielder at short third man for a sharp single, the fielder shies at the non-striker's end but misses
flat trajectory on off stump, Chanderpaul waits for it and drives down the ground for a single
better line and slower through the air on middle and off, defended on the front foot
cut to deep point for  a single
a fraction short again outside off stump and Chanderpaul drives easily through covers
swept down to fine leg for a single, Lara moved across his stumps and he lost balance as he played that stroke
steps down the track and chips over mid-on for a single
pitches short outside the off stumpa nd spins back into Chanderpaul who goes down on one knee and tries to sweep/pull, doesn't make proper contact
fraction wide outside off and Chanderpaul tries to cut, but too hard, he gets an bottom edge past the keeper
an appeal for lbw is turned down because Chanderpaul was struck outside the line of off stump asn he tried to drive that through covers
defended on the front foot on the off side
cut to third man for two runs
dropped slightly short on middle and off, punched off the back foot down to long-on
driven to long on for another single, Hafeez is bowling just too straight at the moment
driven on the front foot through covers for a single
Hafeez drops it short and Lara tries to pull, the ball keeps a bit low and passes under the bottom edge
full ball driven hard on the front foot down to long-off
quick through the air angling into middle and leg stump, driven down the ground to long-on for one
long hop, that's very very short and Chanderpaul lisfts it over square leg for four, that was a gift from the bowler
full ball on off stump, driven back to the bowler who misfields to allow the single
full and wide outside the off stump, driven hard through covers for two more
straying on to middle and leg stump, worked off the pads through midwicket
defended to cover on the front foot
a touch short outside the off stump, Lara cuts but doesn't beat point
dabbed with an open face to short third man
swept down to fine leg for a single
driven back to the bowler on the back foot
outstanding shot, tossed up on middle and stump, Lara converts it into a half-volley by stepping down the pitch and flaying it over cover for four
driven off the front foot to sweeper for a single, Lara now has 10,000 runs in ODIs, that's another milestone in his kitty
cut wide of the fielder at short third man, Razzaq runs around on the fence and stops th boundary
dropped short on off stump, Lara moves forward, waits for it and dabs it behind square for a single
driven down to long on for a single
played off the pads to midwicket for another single
nice drift into the left-hander, Chanderpaul moves across his stumps and gets beaten by the flight, the ball hits the pad
beaten outside the off stump, the batsman wasn't to the pitch of that one and got beaten by the turn
angling across the left hander's off stump, guided down to third man for a single
too straight from Gul, drifting on to the pads, flicked through midwicket for a single
short of a length outside off stump, dabbed short of point for another sharp single
worked off the pads down to fine leg for one more
good length ball on off and middle, Lara tries to drive that too hard and hits it into the ground
pitches short of a length on middle and leg, Lara gets forward and flicks through midwicket for a single to end the over
hits the pad for a leg bye behind square on the leg side
driven wide of the fielder at point
full length ball on off stump, Lara gets on the front foot and blocks it, the batsman race off for a single as the ball rols to short third man
straying on to leg stump, pushed to midwicket for a single
pitches on of stump and moves away from the left-hander, Chanderpaul opens the face and steers it down to third man
driven hard into the ground and back to the bowler, Sami completes a tight over
pitches on middle and leg, the batsman moves across and flicks for a single to square leg
pitches short of a length outside leg stump, Lara waits for it on the back foot and pushes it in front of midwicket for one more
tight line and length, no room for Chanderpaul who defends to point
fullish length angling across the left hadner, Chanderpaul transfers weight on the front foot and drives through cover
short and wide outside the of stump, dabbed down to third man for another single, West Indies are ticking along with the signles but Pakistan won't mind this as long as the boundaries are protected
play and miss outside the off stump, the ball pitches for a second time just before Akmal and he concedes a bye
superb placement, driven just wide of the fielder at mid-on for three, Yousuf fields it just before the fence
pitches on a good length on leg stump, angling across the left hander, Lara tries to force it on the leg side and gets hit on the pad for a leg bye to short third man
another good length delivery on middle and off, driven down the ground for one
pitches on a length on off stump, Chanderpaul lofts it down the ground but it falls short of Razzaq at long-off, he made a hash of that and concedes the extra run
driven down the groud to long-off for a single
the length isn't short enough to cut but Lara cuts anyway, he gets a bottom edge to the keeper
fullish length outside off stump, driven through covers for a single
dabbed to point for a quick single, the fielder shies at the non-striker's end but misses
driven back to Hafeez who dives to his right to stop the single
this time he drives wide of Hafeez for a single to long-off
outstanding save from Inzamam, Lara creamed that to covers and Inzamam dived full length to his left to cut off a boundary
driven through covers for another single
worked through midwicket for a single
short and wide outside off stump, Lara cuts and times it well enough to beat the fielder at third man, presure on the spinner as they get the boundary early in the over
defended to midwicket
quick leg bye taken to short fine leg, the throw comes in and hits the stump at the wicketkeeper's end but the batsman is safe
drifting into Chanderpaul from over the ball hits th pad and goes to square leg
worked off the pads through midwicket, Chanderpaul is havingtrouble moving his feet
driven back to the bowler, the ball hits the stumps at the non-striker's end but Rana Naved didn't get a touch on that
full ball, swinging back into Chanderpaul's pads, he flicks it down to fine leg for a single, he moves into the 90s
slower ball outside off stump, Lara shapes to cut but is beaten by the change of pace, he gets a bottom edge that goes on the bounce to Akmal

bowled him! Huge huge wicket for Pakistan, full ball on leg stump, Lara backed away to make room but was still cramped for space as the ball followed him, Lara then tried to heave it on the leg side but the ball hit the pad before crashing into the stumps
full length and once more Rana Naved gets it to swing back into the right-hander, perhaps it's the change of ball that's doing the trick, Ramdin gets hit on the pads
defended on the back foot to cover
slightly short on off stump, Chanderpaul moves across - he struggles to do so because of his injury - and works it through midwicket
width offered outside the off stump, cut through cover point for a single
tossed up outside off stump, Chanderpaul paddles it down to fine leg for another single, Pakistan won't mind this at all, the boundaries are few and far between
DROPPED! what a shocker from Shoaib Malik at long-off, Ramdin lofted that tamely down the ground, it was a dolly of a catch and it popped it and then out of Malik's hands, embarassing stuff

caught, this time Rehman takes it off his own bowling, poor shot selection from Ramdin as he doesn't get to the pitch of the ball and chips it softly back to Rehman, West Indies are sinking now and fast
pitches outside off stump and spins away from the right-hander, left alone by the batsman
pitches on middle and off and angles across Chanderpaul who is really struggling with his fitness, he doesn't get into position and dabs it to point
slower ball on middle and off stump, defended back to the bowler
fullish length on off stump, driven to deep point for one more
tight line and length around Morton's off stump, he can't do much more than get on the front foot and defend
pushed to mid-off for a quick single
worked off the pads down to fine leg for another single
pitches on a length on off stump, Chanderpaul stands motionless and drives down the ground for one
defended to cover on the front foot
superb slower ball, he took the pace off that by rolling his fingers over it and Morton was foxed
another slower ball, Morton tried to cut that but got a thick bottom edge into the ground
pushed to mid-off on the front foot
width offered outside the off stump, cut past point for a single to end the over
full length outside the off stump, Chanderpaul leans forward and drivs to covers for one more to move on to 97
short of a length outside off stump, Morton drives to mid-off on the back foot

full toss on leg stump, Chanderpaul moves across his stumps once more and flicks wide of the fielder at fine leg for four, he reaches his hundred with that shot, it's been a tough and hard fought innings
hundred and ....out! Rana Naved banged that short and Chanderpaul tried to pull on the front foot, the resulting top edge flew straight to Yasir Hameed at deep midwicket
the yorker, the perfect ball at the deat and it's spot on, the batsman digs it out
another one in the blockhole, Morton can't to anything but defend, excellent bowling
hits a good length and swings it back into the right-hander from off  stump, Smith gets hit on the pad
another inswinger beats smith, the ball hits the pad for a leg bye to third man
full outside off stump, slogged down to long-on for a single
full toss, that swung into Smith quite a bit and hit him on the pad
full ball in the blockhole, dug out to long-on for a single
another full toss, swinging into the right-hander from outside off stump, Smith drives to long-off for one
plumb! superb death bowling from Rana Naved, he bowls that full and nearly in the blockhole, it swings into Smith and hits him on the boot, simple decision for the umpire
Rana Naved oversteps and drifts on to the pad, Mohammed misses the flicks and gets a leg bye to midwicket
slower ball and thwack! Morton got under that full length delivery and slammed it over the long-on fence, powerful shot

well that's four leg byes, and very curious leg byes, Rana Naved fired that into Morton's pads, the batsman scrambled to get out of the way, the ball hit one pad and ricocheted on to the other and then ran past Kamran Akmal for four
driven down the ground to long-off
driven back to the bowler, Rana Naved collects it and flings it back at the stumps, the batsmen steal an overthrow
full ball slanting into the pads, West Indies finish the innings with a leg bye

inn2.comm: starts off with a with a full pitched delivery outside the off stump, hint of swing but Hafeez misses out on some easy runs
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away from the right-hander, no shot offered
punched away through point and Hafeez is off the mark
short of a good length delivery on the stumps, Akmal gets behind the line and defends it with a straight bat
short and bit of width offered, Akmal plays late and chops it down to third man for an easy single - solid shot
good length but again bit wide outside the off stump, Powell getting the ball to shape away nicely
beauty! good length delivery, in the channel and shaping away late. Hafeez goes for the drive and the ball zips past the outside edge - apart from the no-ball a good over to start with
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Akmla slashes hard at it, ball clips the outside edge and flies down to the third man fence - cheaky but they all count
left alone outside the off stump
defended outside the off stump
off-cutter. Akmla gets right behind the line and taps it away towards cover point
watchfully played away on the off side
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven off the back-foot but straight to the fielder at cover
in the channel, no swing but a straight delivery. Hafeez gets a good stride in and pushes it away towards cover
short ball, on the stumps and Hafeez is cramped for room but he goes for the pull, not a well timed shot and the ball rolls away straight to the fielder at midwicket
good length delivery outside the off stump. Excellent line and length. Hafeez shoulders arms and the ball goes through to the keeper
good length, hint of away swing and Hafeez leaves it through
